9:
...Did your senses get sharper or
something?
13:
Haha, I'm afraid my encounters with
a certain little lady have toughened
me up.
22: Time to wrap things up! Nimbus! Alk!
32:
Wow... You were strong enough to
begin with, but now you're just
something else...
35:
I don't know if even Nimbus could
take you anymore.
39: Oh, shut it. You don't gotta rub it in.
42:
...Sure, you've gotten tougher, but
have you fixed your bad habits too?
55: Why are there so many of them...
57:
Idiot! We can't give up yet! What
about your newborn son?
59:
I-it's not like I WANT to give up, but
how...
68:
I'm sure he'd like his father home
safe and sound.
72: Let me mop up this mess for you!
76:
More friends? Now we can have
ourselves a party... Haha!
94:
Thank you so much! We owe you our
lives!
97:
No worries, it's all going to be okay
now. We'll let the Guild know what
happened.
99:
You should head home for now and
rest up.
103: My, my. Someone's in a bad mood.
116:
You're not relying on us much in
combat, are you?
119:
Are you still planning on doing
something stupid like letting
yourself disappear in a fight?
122:
You've got people waiting for you
back home, too. You know?
126: There, there. It’ll be all right.
135:
What's wrong with a simple head
pat, kitten?
143: I am relying on you, you know.
146:
Whenever I fight, I know you two
have got my back.
148:
If I didn't think so, I'd at least hesitate
a little.
155:
Not too honest about your feelings,
are you, kitten?
164: And... It's exactly as you said.
170:
I do indeed have others waiting for
me.
